[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH's 2\C bid is Stayman, asking for a 4-card Major.

NORTH's 2\D bid denies four cards in either Major.

SOUTH knows there is no 8-card Major fit. He also knows the partnership has at least 26 points 
so he bids 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:QT.KQ93.A52.AT86 A63.A72.JT96.QJ3 KJ8754.86.KQ3.72 92.JT54.874.K954"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1NT pass 2H pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "2c7eaaa8410fbe6e0413a3374bb9c37bffdaa1e168b5b1fb1e8b885962102b2b"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST, with 11 points and six \Ss, knows immediately that the final contract will be 4\S 
since the partners must have at least eight \Ss and at least 26 points.

She concludes that it might be better for EAST to be the Declarer so she bids 2\H 
as a Jacoby Transfer. When EAST makes the required 2\S bid she just bids 4\S which 
closes the auction with EAST as Declarer.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:K75.Q93.K75.AKJ3 A82.82.QT94.9852 643.AKJ765.82.Q7 QJT9.T4.AJ63.T64"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1NT pass 2D pass 2H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "692a30271fae12c6785243e963c862ca33d8ed13bed40b25c4bc9bfd98e71dea"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH knows the partnership has a fit in \Hs since SOUTH 
must have at least a doubleton. He also knows the partnership holds at least 27 points.

He prefers SOUTH be the Declarer, (to protect against 
the opening lead), so he uses a Jacoby Transfer.

The contract might go down if played by NORTH, but is odds on when played by SOUTH.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:AK65.AT4.QJ97.K8 T842.932.A6.AQ62 73.KQ86.K42.JT95 QJ9.J75.T853.743"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1NT pass 2C pass 2S pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "754f7a5cf9d5ff65498e0df99bf0ee58d1580e8b5afe4a28ade5e3dddbec9c62"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST, with 9 points and a 4-card \H suit is just strong 
enough to use Stayman.

WEST shows 4 \Ss and EAST describes her minimum hand with no \S fit by bidding 2NT.

WEST has a maximum 1NT opening and bids 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
